def euler_method(f, n, xa, xb, ya, points_of_interest = [], maxval = 1e9, **kw):
    #print(n, kw)
    yb = -10 ** 9
    step = (xb - xa) / n
    x = [xa]
    y = [ya]
    newx = xa
    newy = ya
    ys = []
    for i in range(n):
        newx, newy = newx + step, newy + step * f(newx, newy)
        if abs(newy) <= maxval:
            y.append(newy)
            x.append(newx)
        for j in points_of_interest:
            if abs(newx - j) <= 1e-7:
                ys.append(round(newy, 7))
        
    plt.plot(x,y, **kw)
    return ys
